{center}
{subhead}Classic CinemaWare Games Remastered{def}
{left}
{pp}
Sept 10 2001
{pp}
Cinemaware and ClickBoom have announced production of Digitally Remastered versions
of Cinemaware classic games for retail release at the request of thousands of 
Cinemaware fans around the world.
{pp}
Each CDROM will be produced for multiple platforms including the PC and the Macintosh
and will sell for around $14.99 to $19.99.
{pp}
The games will retain the classic gameplay of the originals but will feature enhanced
graphics and sound effects to make full use of today's technology.
{pp}
The first title will be an enhanced version of the 1986 classic 'Defender of the Crown'.
The game will feature old Saxon England at civil war, with King Richard murdered, the
knights have chosen you to battle against the Normans. You will compete in tournaments
such as jousts, siege castles, and raid enemy strongholds to regain the crown of England.
{pp}
Other classic titles to be remastered include: The Three Stooges, Wings, SDI, The
King of Chicago, Lorfs of the Rising Sun, Sinbad and the Throne of the Falcon, It
Cam frome the Desert, Antheads and the TV Sports series.
{pp}